6-9. ab . . . fortuna: The preposi- tion ab (a) with a passive verb ordinarily distinguishes the agent (a person) from the means or instrument (a thing). When. as here, it accompanies a oom- mon noun it shows that the thing is personified. a rhetorical figure which is sometimes marked in English by a cap- ital. ‘by Fortune and by Hope.'
